HEADWORD: Scepterellate
<hw>Scep`ter*el"late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a straight shaft with whorls of spines; -- said of certain
sponge spicules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

